					mainPhoto : '',
					mainPhotoAlt : ``,
					instructions : `MadLibs are a word game where one player prompts the other player  to fill in blanks in a story. The other party doesn't know what the story is, so the results can often be pretty hilarious! The game was invented in 1958 in the United States. There are various different MabLibs books available and you can find lots of them online.<br><br>
						<img src="images/tasks/storyteller/family-writing.jpg" alt="mother and daughter writing"><br><br>
						MadLibs are a great way to make up funny, crazy stories that you can use as inspiration to add silly elements to your own stories.`,
